---
import ServiceCityPage from '~/components/pages/ServiceCityPage.astro';
import { services, cities } from '~/data/service-city-config';
---

<ServiceCityPage service={services['generators']} city={cities['grand-rapids-mi']}>
  <section class="container section-pad">
    <h2>Generators for Grand Rapids Homes and Businesses</h2>
    <p>
      Grand Rapids outages tend to hit two very different buildings: older Heritage Hill and Eastown homes on aging
      service, and commercial spaces where a few hours of downtime is real lost revenue. The sizing conversation is
      different for each. A home wants heat, sump, and refrigeration covered; a business wants point-of-sale, walk-in
      coolers, and critical equipment carried without a hiccup.
    </p>
    <p>
      For older homes, the generator interconnect often surfaces a service that should be modernized first — we cover
      that on our <a href="/panel-upgrades-grand-rapids-mi">Grand Rapids panel upgrade page</a>. For commercial standby,
      the load calculation and transfer-switch selection are where the money is made or wasted; we walk the real loads
      before quoting.
    </p>
  </section>
</ServiceCityPage>
